      <p class="hc-rule-note">The rebuy side is yours to set. Leave it <strong>at your sale</strong> for <a href="/wait-or-deploy-now">Wait-or-Deploy</a>&rsquo;s rule &mdash; the first lower entry within two years, no timing, no discretion. Slide to a deeper target and the stats change honestly: bigger multiples when it arrives, arriving less often, after longer waits &mdash; while the trend compounds under the cash. If the target never comes, the cash rebuys at the two-year price, sometimes higher than you sold.</p>
      <p class="hc-couple-note">Deciding the redeploy on its own &mdash; cash in hand, no round trip &mdash; is <a href="/wait-or-deploy-now">Wait, or Deploy Now?</a>&rsquo;s question; this page couples the two ends of the same round trip.</p>

      <!-- both audiences, one passage (§6 + addendum A2/A4): the explorer and the manager -->
      <div class="hc-manager-note">
        <p>Exploring your first split, or tracking one you already made? Set the sell slider to where you actually sold, and the rebuy target to what you&rsquo;re waiting for. Sold, and the price ran past you? You are living the no-arrival branch &mdash; the target never came. This page&rsquo;s honest answer is the two-year rule: at some point the strategy ends and the cash goes back, sometimes above your sale. Deciding when, from here, with cash in hand, is <a href="/wait-or-deploy-now">Wait, or Deploy Now?</a>&rsquo;s question &rarr;</p>
      </div>

